<h2>Please pick vegetarian!</h2><p>In the run up to the Green Formal sign up, I wanted to give you a heads up of what we&rsquo;re trying to do!</p><p>Apart from all decorations being recycled, recyclable or biodegradable for the formal we are asking for you to join us in a meat free Monday for the environment!&nbsp;<br />Meat rearing, production and transportation are a major contributing factors to global carbon emissions. By choosing the vegetarian option for our formal you can make a small step in reducing your meal&rsquo;s carbon foo<span class="text_exposed_show">tprint. Lower carbon emissions however, are not the only reason in how vegetarianism can save the planet. Read more here:</span></p><p><span class="text_exposed_show"><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2010/jul/18/vegetarianism-save-planet-environment" target="_blank">http://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2010/jul/18/vegetarianism-save-planet-environment</a></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Be a fun-gi and join me in a meat free Monday and see you at the formal!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>-Matthew Ricketts</p>